  title="Steps to Register a .ma Domain with Reserved Terms"
  paragraphs={[
    `<span style="color: #022545;">To complete the registration of your domain name containing a reserved term, please submit the following supporting documents by opening a <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a style="color: #022545; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://my.hostino.com/submitticket.php" rel="noopener"><b>support ticket</b></a></span>:</span>`,
    `<ul class="flex mt-[30px] list-dots-paragraph mb-[40px] flex-col gap-y-4 pl-[30px]">
  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
    <span class="w-2 h-2 mt-2 bg-primary rounded-full flex-shrink-0"></span>
    <span><strong>Name of the company or organization</strong> for which this domain name will be registered.</span>
  </li>

  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
    <span class="w-2 h-2 mt-2 bg-primary rounded-full flex-shrink-0"></span>
    <span><strong>Email address, postal address, and phone number</strong> of the company or organization.</span>
  </li>

  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
    <span class="w-2 h-2 mt-2 bg-primary rounded-full flex-shrink-0"></span>
    <span><strong>Reason for registration:</strong> This information will be used to support your request to the ANRT (National Telecommunications Regulatory Agency).</span>
  </li>

  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
    <span class="w-2 h-2 mt-2 bg-primary rounded-full flex-shrink-0"></span>
    <span>
      <strong>Completed, signed, and stamped form</strong> available via this 
      <a style="text-decoration: underline; color: #022545;" href="https://www.hostino.ma/Examen_Prealable_nom_de_domaine_maroc.pdf"><u>link</u></a>.
    </span>
  </li>
</ul>
`,
  ]}
  imageSrc="/images/08/ma-domain-with-reserved-terms.jpg"
  imageAlt="Ma Domain Name With Reserved Terms"

/>
    <TextLeftImageRight
      title=".MA Domain Name Dispute Resolution Service"
      paragraphs={[
        `Managing domain names in Morocco is based on a strict regulatory framework, particularly for the .ma and .المغرب extensions. 1 To ensure effective protection of intellectual property rights, the National Telecommunications Regulatory Agency (ANRT), in collaboration with the <b>World Intellectual Property Organization</b> (WIPO), has established an Alternative Dispute Resolution Procedure (ADRP). This procedure addresses conflicts related to the abusive registration of domain names corresponding to protected trademarks, company names, and geographical indications or designations of origin in Morocco.`,
        "In order to strengthen the protection of businesses and rights holders, the ANRT has recently revised the ADRP regulations. This procedure now covers a broader range of disputes, including those related to domain names registered under the Arabic .المغرب extension. This extension thus benefits from the same level of protection as .ma domains, guaranteeing better legal security for businesses and rights holders."
      ]}
      imageSrc="/images/08/ma-domaine-name-wipo.jpg"
      className="lg:mt-[150px] mt-[80px] mb-[0]"
      consultButtonTextExiste={false}
    />

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <p class="paragraph">
          The new regulations will come into effect on February 15, 2025, and will offer applicants more appropriate remedies to defend their interests. Any person or business facing a domain name dispute in Morocco can consult the details of this procedure and submit a request through the WIPO <b>Arbitration and Mediation Center</b>.
        </p>
        <p class="paragraph">
         or more information, please refer to the full regulations on the official WIPO website: <a href="https://www.wipo.int/amc/fr/domains/cctld/ma/index.html" rel="noopener"><u>Link to the regulations</u></a>.
        </p>
       
      </div>
    </section>

